WEBVTT

00:06.000 --> 00:12.074
Advertise your product or brand here
contact www.OpenSubtitles.org today

01:54.865 --> 01:57.113
(BOAT WHISTLE BLOWING)

02:06.668 --> 02:08.495
(MEN SHOUTING IN CHINESE)

02:09.253 --> 02:12.458
Come on, lads, hurry!
We haven't got all day.

02:14.843 --> 02:17.386
Is that it, captain? Are we here?

02:17.387 --> 02:20.139
Aye, laddie. That's
Bangkok all right.

02:20.140 --> 02:22.892
ANNA: Louis! Oh, Louis!

02:22.893 --> 02:25.186
Mother! Look, there's Bangkok.

02:25.187 --> 02:28.140
Yes, I know. Isn't it exciting?

02:28.482 --> 02:32.109
Captain, I heard them lowering
the anchor. Is anything wrong?

02:32.110 --> 02:35.529
We have to wait for the afternoon
tide to carry us over the bar.

02:35.530 --> 02:37.403
Oh, I see.

02:41.370 --> 02:44.538
Will the king of Siam come
down to meet us, Mother?

02:44.539 --> 02:47.708
I hardly think so, dear.
Kings don't, as a rule.

02:47.709 --> 02:51.004
(MEN SHOUTING IN CHINESE)

02:53.382 --> 02:56.092
Come forward, lads.
They need help in the bow.

02:56.093 --> 02:57.715
Get along there.

02:59.971 --> 03:01.297
That's the royal barge.

03:06.937 --> 03:09.397
The king is coming out to meet us.

03:09.398 --> 03:11.817
It's not the king,
it's the kralahome.

03:11.858 --> 03:13.734
ANNA: Who is the kralahome?

03:13.735 --> 03:15.861
ORTON: A sort of a prime minister.

03:15.862 --> 03:18.941
The king's right-hand
man, you might say.

03:19.282 --> 03:22.410
May I look? Please, may I see?

03:22.411 --> 03:24.079
Aye, laddie.

03:24.496 --> 03:29.042
Ma'am, if I might be allowed to
offer you a word of warning,

03:29.292 --> 03:32.670
that man has power, and he can
use it for you or against you.

03:32.671 --> 03:35.670
You must stop worrying about me,
Captain Orton.

03:35.841 --> 03:38.759
Sometimes I wonder if you know what
you're really facing.

03:38.760 --> 03:41.262
An Englishwoman alone
in a country like Siam.

03:41.263 --> 03:44.098
It doesn't matter, captain.
I shall have work to do,

03:44.099 --> 03:47.059
and the king has promised me
a house of my own.

03:47.060 --> 03:50.764
I'll have a place to bring up my boy
as his father would have wished.

03:50.981 --> 03:54.734
Mother, look. The prime
minister is naked!

03:54.735 --> 03:58.237
Oh, don't be ridiculous, Louis.
He can't be naked.

03:58.238 --> 03:59.940
He's only...

04:00.657 --> 04:02.325
half-naked.

04:04.119 --> 04:06.788
They look so cruel, Mother.

04:07.247 --> 04:09.950
Father wouldn't have liked us
to be afraid, would he?

04:10.000 --> 04:13.419
No, Louis. Father would not have
liked us to be afraid.

04:13.420 --> 04:15.629
Not ever.

04:15.630 --> 04:17.757
Doesn't anything ever frighten you?

04:17.757 --> 04:19.255
Oh, yes, sometimes.

04:19.301 --> 04:21.673
- What do you do?
- I whistle.

04:22.179 --> 04:24.507
Oh, that's why you whistle.

04:25.098 --> 04:27.517
That's why I whistle.

04:28.602 --> 04:31.145
(SINGING) Whenever I feel afraid

04:31.146 --> 04:33.599
I hold my head erect

04:33.732 --> 04:38.444
And whistle a happy tune,
So no one will suspect

04:38.445 --> 04:41.068
I'm afraid

04:41.323 --> 04:44.033
While shivering in my shoes

04:44.034 --> 04:46.702
I strike a careless pose

04:46.703 --> 04:48.913
And whistle a happy tune

04:48.914 --> 04:53.164
And no one ever knows I'm afraid

04:54.753 --> 04:57.379
The result of this deception

04:57.380 --> 04:59.878
is very strange to tell

04:59.925 --> 05:02.885
For when I fool the people I fear

05:02.886 --> 05:05.259
I fool myself as well!

05:05.430 --> 05:08.015
I whistle a happy tune

05:08.016 --> 05:10.768
And ev'ry single time

05:10.769 --> 05:13.354
The happiness in the tune

05:13.355 --> 05:17.856
Convinces me that I'm not afraid.

05:19.069 --> 05:21.362
Make believe you're brave

05:21.363 --> 05:24.066
And the trick will take you far.

05:24.324 --> 05:26.742
You may be as brave

05:26.743 --> 05:29.492
As you make believe you are.

05:29.830 --> 05:31.907
(WHISTLING)

05:35.126 --> 05:38.125
You may be as brave

05:38.171 --> 05:41.545
As you make believe you are.

05:46.012 --> 05:51.225
(SPEAKING) I think that's a very
good idea, Mother. A very good idea.

05:51.226 --> 05:54.395
Yes, it is a good idea, isn't it?

05:54.396 --> 05:58.317
I don't think I shall
ever be afraid again.

05:58.358 --> 05:59.608
Good.

05:59.609 --> 06:02.194
BOTH (SINGING):
The result of this deception

06:02.195 --> 06:04.989
ls very strange to tell

06:04.990 --> 06:07.825
For when I fool the people I fear

06:07.826 --> 06:09.903
I fool myself as well!

06:13.707 --> 06:15.409
(WHISTLING)

06:18.962 --> 06:20.914
(KRALAHOME SPEAKS CHINESE)

06:30.891 --> 06:32.766
This is Anna Leonowens.

06:32.767 --> 06:36.562
Mrs. Leonowens, may I present
His Excellency, the kralahome.

06:39.733 --> 06:44.737
Sir, you are lady who will be
schoolmistress of the royal children?

06:44.738 --> 06:46.697
- Yes.
- He called you "sir."

06:46.698 --> 06:48.073
Hush, dear, hush.

06:48.074 --> 06:50.242
Have you friends in Bangkok?

06:50.243 --> 06:53.071
I know no one in Bangkok at all.

06:53.079 --> 06:54.451
(SPEAKING CHINESE)

06:59.252 --> 07:03.213
His Excellency wishes to know,
are you married, sir?

07:03.214 --> 07:04.791
I am a widow.

07:04.841 --> 07:08.594
What manner of man,
your deceased husband?

07:08.595 --> 07:12.800
My husband was an officer
of Her Majesty's Army in...

07:14.184 --> 07:16.101
Tell your master his
business with me

07:16.102 --> 07:18.646
is as schoolteacher to
the royal children.

07:18.772 --> 07:21.440
He has no right to pry
into my personal affairs.

07:21.441 --> 07:23.314
He hasn't, Captain Orton.

07:30.659 --> 07:32.368
I don't like that man.

07:32.369 --> 07:36.664
In foreign country is best
you like everyone until you leave.

07:36.665 --> 07:40.209
You might at least have told us
you speak English, Your Excellency.

07:40.210 --> 07:44.665
It is not necessary for schoolteacher
to know everything at once.

07:44.714 --> 07:46.465
You come with me now.

07:46.466 --> 07:49.301
Your baggages shall be carried
to palace later.

07:49.302 --> 07:53.681
Just a minute. Not the palace.
I am not living in the palace.

07:53.682 --> 07:56.852
- Who say?
- The king say... Says.

07:56.893 --> 08:00.142
In his letter of agreement,
he promised me 20£ a month

08:00.146 --> 08:02.974
and a house of my own
outside the palace walls.

08:03.108 --> 08:06.026
King do not always remember
what he promise.

08:06.027 --> 08:08.404
Then you will have to remind him.

08:08.405 --> 08:12.241
If I tell king he break this
promise, I will make anger in him.

08:12.242 --> 08:16.787
I think is better if king's anger
reserved for more important matters.

08:16.788 --> 08:20.249
Very well, then. If you are
afraid to tell him, I will.

08:20.250 --> 08:23.252
I should like to see him at once,
while there's time for me

08:23.253 --> 08:25.330
to return to England on this boat.

08:25.422 --> 08:27.840
- King very busy now.
- Your Excellency,

08:27.841 --> 08:30.843
all I want is
a few minutes' audience with him.

08:30.844 --> 08:33.511
I have come here to work
and I intend to work,

08:33.513 --> 08:37.182
but I shall take nothing less
than I have been promised.

08:37.183 --> 08:39.385
You will tell king this?

08:39.977 --> 08:42.020
I will tell king this.

08:42.022 --> 08:45.649
It should be very
interesting meeting.

08:45.650 --> 08:47.318
You come now!

08:48.445 --> 08:50.070
If you change your mind...

08:50.071 --> 08:53.115
Goodbye, Captain Orton,
and thank you for everything.

08:53.116 --> 08:54.283
Good luck, ma'am.

08:54.284 --> 08:56.201
- Goodbye, captain.
- Goodbye, laddie.

08:56.202 --> 08:58.621
Take good care of your mother, now.

09:03.501 --> 09:04.998
(WHISTLING)

09:12.802 --> 09:14.424
(CHATTERING)

10:52.110 --> 10:54.859
King in bad spirit today.

10:54.946 --> 10:58.240
Suggest schoolteacher
wait for better day.

10:58.241 --> 11:01.910
My spirit is just as bad,
Your Excellency. I cannot wait.

11:01.911 --> 11:04.034
(BELL GONGS)

11:30.440 --> 11:34.860
Man is Lun Tha,
emissary from court of Burma.

11:34.861 --> 11:38.697
He bring present to king
from prince of Burma.

11:38.698 --> 11:41.200
Her name is Tuptim.

11:41.201 --> 11:43.995
Why, that girl is a present?

11:44.537 --> 11:45.989
For king.

12:18.071 --> 12:21.115
King is pleased with her.

12:29.207 --> 12:30.624
(BELL GONGS)

12:32.502 --> 12:36.047
Sorry. King has concluded audience.

12:36.089 --> 12:38.382
Well, you mean I cannot see him?

12:38.383 --> 12:40.301
Not today.

12:41.469 --> 12:43.888
Louis, come with me.

12:46.516 --> 12:47.933
(CHATTERING)

12:48.393 --> 12:50.220
KRALAHOME: You cannot do this!

12:56.401 --> 12:58.402
- ANNA: Your Majesty.
- Who, who, who?

12:58.403 --> 13:01.571
Your Majesty, is new
English schoolteacher.

13:01.572 --> 13:03.865
Mrs. Anna Leonowens and son.

13:03.866 --> 13:06.239
ANNA: Louis Leonowens.

13:07.954 --> 13:10.247
You are schoolteacher?

13:10.248 --> 13:14.876
Yes, Your Majesty. But before I start
my work here, there is one point...

13:14.877 --> 13:18.088
You are part of general plan I have
for bringing to Siam

13:18.089 --> 13:20.590
what is good in Western culture.

13:20.591 --> 13:24.386
Already I have bring printing
press here for printing.

13:24.387 --> 13:27.010
- Yes, I know, Your Majesty.
- How you know?

13:27.557 --> 13:32.684
Before I signed our agreement, I found
out about your ambitions for Siam.

13:33.313 --> 13:34.685
(SCOFFS)

13:37.817 --> 13:39.940
How old shall you be?

13:40.278 --> 13:43.238
You do not look like
scientific person for teaching.

13:43.239 --> 13:44.941
How old shall you be?

13:45.575 --> 13:48.699
I am 150 years old, Your Majesty.

13:50.997 --> 13:52.995
In what year were you borned?

13:54.125 --> 13:58.125
In 1712, Your Majesty.

14:02.425 --> 14:05.802
How many years
shall you have been married?

14:05.803 --> 14:08.176
Several, Your Majesty.

14:12.769 --> 14:15.437
How many grandchildren
shall you have by now?

14:15.438 --> 14:17.773
How many, how many, how many?

14:17.774 --> 14:19.107
You do not answer fast.

14:19.108 --> 14:21.151
I make better question
than she make answer.

14:21.152 --> 14:23.354
(LAUGHING)

14:27.492 --> 14:30.320
You are not afraid of king.

14:30.953 --> 14:35.457
Not to be afraid is good thing
in scientific mind.

14:35.458 --> 14:38.707
I think maybe

14:38.795 --> 14:41.171
you make very good schoolteaching.

14:41.172 --> 14:42.419
Come.

14:46.010 --> 14:47.507
(CHATTERING)

14:48.471 --> 14:50.173
(BELL GONGS)

14:57.855 --> 14:59.898
A few of my wives.

14:59.899 --> 15:03.068
They have beauty
but not gift for knowledge.

15:03.069 --> 15:06.864
I have no time for teaching,
being busy with foreign affairs

15:06.865 --> 15:09.032
and other situations.

15:09.700 --> 15:13.370
I may present Lady
Thiang, head wife.

15:15.081 --> 15:20.001
(SINGING)
There is a happy land far, far away

15:20.002 --> 15:22.796
Where saints in glory stand

15:22.797 --> 15:26.217
Bright, bright as day.

15:27.009 --> 15:31.346
(SPEAKING) "In the beginning, God
created the heaven and the earth."

15:31.347 --> 15:33.049
Missionary.

15:33.057 --> 15:35.976
Oh, a missionary
taught you English.

15:35.977 --> 15:39.147
Yes, sir. Missionary.

15:39.272 --> 15:41.395
I have boy too.

15:41.399 --> 15:45.902
Crown Prince Chowfa
Chulalongkorn, heir to throne.

15:45.903 --> 15:48.196
You help Madam Leonowens
with schoolteaching

15:48.197 --> 15:51.697
and she in turn shall teach
you the better English.

15:53.703 --> 15:56.455
She is very grateful
to me for my kindness.

15:56.456 --> 16:01.082
Lady Thiang, have children prepare
for presentation to schoolteacher.

16:02.378 --> 16:05.088
Speaking of teaching, Your Majesty,
in our agreement...

16:05.089 --> 16:07.883
Lady Son Klin, Lady
Talap, Lady Piam.

16:08.009 --> 16:12.134
And this girl is present to me
from a Burma prince.

16:12.221 --> 16:13.513
She just arrived.

16:13.556 --> 16:15.258
Good day, madam.

16:15.391 --> 16:20.188
My name is Tuptim.
I already speak English.

16:20.313 --> 16:22.731
And very nicely too.

16:22.732 --> 16:25.400
I think I have fine idea.

16:25.401 --> 16:28.737
In addition to children, you will
also teach those of my wives

16:28.738 --> 16:30.739
as have sense enough for learning.

16:30.740 --> 16:33.783
Siam to be very modern,
scientific country.

16:33.784 --> 16:35.861
Everybody speaking the English.

16:35.995 --> 16:40.457
Your Majesty, it is not in our
agreement that I teach your wives too.

16:40.458 --> 16:44.753
Also, I will allow you to help me
in my foreign correspondence.

16:44.754 --> 16:47.756
I shall be perfectly happy
to help you in any way I can

16:47.757 --> 16:51.426
provided we can clear up this
one little matter of the house.

16:51.427 --> 16:52.970
House?

16:53.095 --> 16:54.429
House? What house?

16:54.430 --> 16:58.350
My house, Your Majesty. The one you
promised me, adjoining the palace.

16:58.351 --> 17:01.645
It is a pleasure that you
shall live in palace.

17:01.646 --> 17:04.520
You teach in palace,
and you shall live in palace.

17:04.982 --> 17:09.109
Will have nice apartment.
Can look out, see many things.

17:09.111 --> 17:11.613
Oh, yes, I'm sure we
could see many things,

17:11.614 --> 17:16.194
such as iron bars, guards at the
doors, et cetera, et cetera.

17:17.286 --> 17:19.329
What is this "et cetera"?

17:21.457 --> 17:25.377
Well, it means "and all the rest
and so forth," Your Majesty.

17:25.962 --> 17:27.334
(BELL GONGS)

17:27.880 --> 17:29.297
You will meet my children.

17:29.298 --> 17:32.467
I'm sorry, Your Majesty,
but if there is to be no house,

17:32.468 --> 17:34.844
I shall have to get
back to the boat.

17:34.845 --> 17:38.390
You will stand here and
meet royal children.

17:43.521 --> 17:45.769
Very well, Your Majesty.

17:46.816 --> 17:49.269
But there isn't much time.

17:49.986 --> 17:51.358
(BELL GONGS)

17:54.574 --> 17:57.698
The royal princes and princesses.

19:21.661 --> 19:23.363
(GRUNTS)

21:28.370 --> 21:29.913
Well, well, Well?

21:56.357 --> 21:57.900
(CHILDREN SIGHING)

21:58.734 --> 22:02.654
Schoolteacher has graciously changed
her mind and shall live in palace.

22:02.655 --> 22:05.608
For the time being, Your Majesty.

22:05.616 --> 22:07.909
These are the children
you shall teach.

22:07.910 --> 22:10.912
Someday shall allow you
to meet my others.

22:10.913 --> 22:12.956
More, Your Majesty?

22:12.957 --> 22:15.667
Children of wives not
in favor with king.

22:15.668 --> 22:17.752
Sixty-seven, I think.

22:17.753 --> 22:19.125
Oh.

22:24.301 --> 22:25.548
Hmm.

22:32.852 --> 22:34.144
(CHATTERING)

22:34.436 --> 22:39.023
No! Oh, ladies, please.
Don't open that, no.

22:39.024 --> 22:42.979
Oh, my goodness! Oh, won't you all
go back to your rooms?

22:43.070 --> 22:45.363
Lady Thiang, will you please
ask them to leave?

22:45.364 --> 22:47.657
I must have some privacy.

22:47.658 --> 22:49.485
(SPEAKING CHINESE)

22:58.961 --> 23:01.664
Good heavens!
What are they trying to do to me?

23:01.755 --> 23:06.134
Sir, they think you wear dress like
that because you shaped like that.

23:06.135 --> 23:08.588
Well, I most certainly am not.

23:08.971 --> 23:10.798
(WOMEN GASPING)

23:11.473 --> 23:13.975
They wish to know, sir,
if they may see the boy?

23:13.976 --> 23:16.394
I'm sorry, Lady
Thiang, he is asleep.

23:16.395 --> 23:20.648
Please, do tell me.
Why do you keep calling me sir?

23:20.649 --> 23:25.104
Because you scientific,
not lowly like woman.

23:25.321 --> 23:29.196
But do you all think
that women are more lowly than men?

23:29.325 --> 23:32.410
(SPEAKING CHINESE)

23:32.411 --> 23:34.495
Well, I certainly do not.

23:34.496 --> 23:38.666
Please, sir, do not tell king.
Make king angry.

23:38.667 --> 23:41.836
Perhaps it's time somebody
did tell him a thing or two.

23:41.837 --> 23:43.459
TUPTIM: Mrs. Anna?

23:43.672 --> 23:47.675
Please, you have some English books
I can read?

23:47.676 --> 23:51.597
Yes, of course, my dear,
but they're not unpacked yet.

23:58.020 --> 24:00.723
They laugh at her
because she is foolish child.

24:00.898 --> 24:04.692
She has come to live in palace
of king and yet she is unhappy.

24:04.693 --> 24:07.236
After all, she had no
choice in the matter.

24:07.237 --> 24:09.735
Perhaps she is homesick.

24:13.577 --> 24:17.080
Is not homesickness that
make me sad, Mrs. Anna.

24:17.081 --> 24:20.041
Is love for one I shall
never see again.

24:20.042 --> 24:21.417
Oh, poor child.

24:21.418 --> 24:25.213
He is Lun Tha,
who was chosen to bring me here.

24:25.214 --> 24:28.383
We tried so hard
not to have love for each other

24:28.384 --> 24:31.133
but we could not help ourselves.

24:31.220 --> 24:33.471
We did try, Mrs. Anna.

24:33.472 --> 24:38.101
It isn't easy to stop loving a
man if he's the man you want.

24:38.102 --> 24:41.306
Even if you know you will
never see him again.

24:41.981 --> 24:43.649
I know.

24:44.066 --> 24:47.611
I was very much in
love with my husband.

24:47.778 --> 24:49.696
(WOMEN CHATTERING)

24:53.242 --> 24:55.451
Please ask them to put that down.

24:55.452 --> 24:58.826
They wish to know, sir, who is man?

24:59.832 --> 25:03.536
That was my husband, Tom.

25:05.754 --> 25:07.296
- ALL: Tom.
- Mm-hmm.

25:07.297 --> 25:09.340
He was pretty in face.

25:09.341 --> 25:13.842
Oh, dear, yes, he was.
Very pretty in face.

25:16.098 --> 25:20.143
(SINGING) When I think of Tom

25:20.144 --> 25:22.854
I think about a night

25:22.855 --> 25:26.107
When the earth smelled of summer

25:26.108 --> 25:29.318
And the sky was streaked with white

25:29.319 --> 25:33.031
And the soft mist of England

25:33.032 --> 25:36.117
Was sleeping on a hill,

25:36.118 --> 25:40.744
I remember this

25:41.165 --> 25:47.543
And I always will.

25:49.798 --> 25:53.134
There are new lovers now

25:53.135 --> 25:57.135
On the same silent hill

25:57.139 --> 26:02.812
Looking on the same blue sea,

26:03.395 --> 26:07.315
And I know Tom and I

26:07.316 --> 26:11.152
are a part of them all,

26:11.153 --> 26:16.530
And they're all a part of Tom

26:17.493 --> 26:23.291
and me.

26:25.709 --> 26:31.547
Hello, young lovers,
whoever you are,

26:31.548 --> 26:37.630
I hope your troubles are few.

26:38.222 --> 26:45.431
All my good wishes
go with you tonight.

26:46.021 --> 26:51.067
I've been in love like you.

26:51.068 --> 26:54.028
Be brave, young lovers,

26:54.029 --> 26:56.903
and follow your star,

26:57.116 --> 27:02.743
Be brave and faithful and true,

27:03.580 --> 27:06.290
Cling very close

27:06.291 --> 27:10.997
to each other tonight.

27:11.213 --> 27:16.544
I've been in love like you.

27:16.635 --> 27:21.764
I know how it feels
to have wings on your heels

27:21.765 --> 27:26.769
And to fly down a
street in a trance.

27:26.770 --> 27:32.272
You fly down a street
on the chance that you'll meet,

27:32.568 --> 27:34.862
And you meet

27:35.404 --> 27:41.327
not really by chance.

27:42.452 --> 27:49.001
Don't cry, young
lovers whatever you do

27:49.084 --> 27:54.791
Don't cry because I'm alone,

27:56.008 --> 27:58.885
All of my mem'ries

27:58.886 --> 28:03.637
are happy tonight,

28:03.974 --> 28:09.351
I've had a love of my own,

28:09.605 --> 28:14.108
I've had a love of my own,

28:14.109 --> 28:17.483
like yours,

28:17.487 --> 28:21.282
I've had a love

28:21.909 --> 28:29.118
of my own.

